com.sand.count21.logiikka

Class Player

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sand.count21.logiikka.Player

  • public class Player
extends Object
    This class is the player in the game. The player knows his own cards and can count the values of the cards using Blackjack rules.

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructor and Description
      Player()
      Default constructor for the player.
      Player(int money)
      This constructor makes it possible to construct a player with more money than the default value 100.

      • totalValueOfCardsAceLow

        public int totalValueOfCardsAceLow()
        This method calculates the total value of cards in the players hand. The ace has the value 1 and every face card has the value 10.
        Returns:
        the total value of the cards

      • totalValueOfCardsAceHigh

        public int totalValueOfCardsAceHigh()
        This method calculates the total value of the cards in the players hand. The ace has the value 11 and every face card has the value 10. If there is more aces than one in the hand then only one ace is counted as 11, the other aces are counted as one.
        Returns:
        The total value of the cards in hand. Ace is 11 and Facecard 10
